    "body": "I am hit by a very similar problem on Windows 10 + electron 1.0.1 and 1.0.2 (I haven't tried 1.1.0 because it currently does not work with Windows 10).\n\nAs part of my electron app, I am using electron-sudo.exec which eventually calls child_process.execSync().  This function then run following which causes the exception.\n\n```\n if (inheritStderr)\n    process.stderr.write(ret.stderr);\n```\n\nHere is the full call stack.\n\n```\nfs.js:706 Uncaught Error: EPERM: operation not permitted, write\nfs.writeSync    @   fs.js:706\nSyncWriteStream.write   @   fs.js:2064\nexecSync    @   child_process.js:519\nwriteTempBatchFile  @   E:\\kdinstall-win32-x64\\resources\\app\\node_modules\\electron-sudo\\index.js:12\nattempt @   E:\\kdinstall-win32-x64\\resources\\app\\node_modules\\electron-sudo\\index.js:89\nexec    @   E:\\kdinstall-win32-x64\\resources\\app\\node_modules\\electron-sudo\\index.js:206\nAppComponent.install    @   app.component.ts:355\n```\n\nMore detailed version info..\n\n```\nares:\"1.10.1-DEV\"\natom-shell:\"1.0.1\"\nchrome:\"49.0.2623.75\"\nelectron:\"1.0.1\"\nhttp_parser:\"2.6.2\"\nmodules:\"47\"\nnode:\"5.10.0\"\nopenssl:\"1.0.2g\"\nuv:\"1.8.0\"\nv8:\"4.9.385.28\"\nzlib:\"1.2.8\"\n```\n"
